  "prompt": "How is WIND Mobile so cheap?",
  "response": "WIND Mobile (now Freedom Mobile, owned by Shaw Communications) was able to offer cheaper plans through several strategies:\n\n1. Limited network infrastructure: Initially, they had fewer cell towers and coverage compared to major carriers\n\n2. Using AWS (Advanced Wireless Spectrum) spectrum, which was cheaper to acquire\n\n3. Targeting urban areas with more concentrated populations\n\n4. Lower overhead and marketing costs compared to larger national carriers\n\n5. Offering more flexible, no-contract plans\n\n6. Focusing on price-sensitive customers who prioritize cost over extensive coverage\n\n7. Leveraging wholesale network agreements\n\nAfter being acquired by Shaw Communications in 2016, they've continued to offer competitive pricing while expanding their network infrastructure. The company rebranded to Freedom Mobile in 2016 but maintained their strategy of offering affordable wireless services.",
